Description.div:
On the following pages you will be asked %System_NumberOfQuestions% questions about Responsible Officers for APRA.
You will be asked multiple choice questions. Answer each question by clicking the button to the left of the most appropriate response.

div.font: After you answer the last question, you will be given the chance to review and then submit your answers.

Description.div: Please note that if you exit the quiz before clicking the Submit Answers button then your answers will not be saved.
To move between questions, use the ◄ and ► navigation buttons on the bottom right of the page.

Description.strong: What is the main purpose of the RO in the context of the APRA regime?

Answer.Description: To make the government seem effective
To fulfil the recommendations of the Wallis Inquiry into the financial system
To enable the RSE licensee to demonstrate that its senior people satisfy the Fit and Proper Test under the SIS Act
To create work for lawyers

strong.strong: The ROs and RMs under ASIC and APRA are different under the SIS Act and Corporations Act, but do relate to senior people within the entity. True or false?

Answer.Description: True
False

strong.strong: The main differences between an APRA RO and an ASIC RM are that…

Answer.Description: … an ASIC RM can deal in any securities or financial products whereas an APRA RO can only deal with services and products listed under the SIS Act
… an ASIC RM is recognised under the AFS licensing scheme whereas the APRA RO is recognised under the RSE licensing scheme
… an ASIC RM can only be penalised under the Corporations Act whereas an APRA RO can be penalised under both the Corporations Act and the SIS Act
… they are the same position

strong.strong: What key information must an applicant supply to APRA before APRA will grant an RSE licence?

Answer.Description: Adequate capital resources, integrating fit and proper person test into policy, risk management strategies, up to date CV, material outsourcing of agreements
Fit and proper standard, material outsourcing of agreements, adequacy of human, technological and financial resources, risk management strategy, risk management plan
Necessary skills and knowledge of investment, outsourcing of skills, risk management strategy, adequate capital resources, fit and proper standard, knowledge of necessary legislation
None of the above

strong.strong: APRA’s ultimate goal in administering the RSE licensing regime is to promote high standards of compliance, risk management and governance within the superannuation industry. True or false?

Answer.Description: True
False

strong.strong: The Corporations Act requires that directors must…

Answer.Description: … use their business judgment, act with care and diligence, use propriety and must not misuse sensitive information for their own purposes or criminal activities
… take reasonable care and diligence, act in good faith in the best interests of the corporation and for a proper purpose, not misuse position to their own advantage, not misuse information
… must use their business judgment to the level of someone who is in the same position as them, must not misuse information, must act with care and honesty and must act in a 'fit and proper' manner
… must not insider trade or breach the business judgment rule

strong.strong: What factors does APRA take into account when considering an individual's propriety?

Answer.Description: Character, competence, diligence, experience, honesty, integrity, judgement
Truthfulness, experience, curriculum vitae, character references, competitiveness
Character, competence, truthfulness, honesty, reputation, experience
Character, competence, willingness, management experience, education

strong.strong: The Prudential Practice Guide requires all responsible officers to satisfy the fitness and propriety standard to same level. True or false?

Answer.Description: True
False

strong.strong: Responsible officers and responsible managers are prohibited from having insurance cover. True or false?

Answer.Description: True
False
